The paper proposes a new algorithm for reinforcement learning that improves upon existing trajectory optimization algorithms. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the algorithm involves backpropagation, which is a common technique in neural networks, further supporting the likelihood of cs.LG or cs.AI. The algorithm also deals with system dynamics, suggesting that it may belong to the robotics (cs.RO) or control systems (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves Q-functions, which are commonly used in reinforcement learning, further supporting the likelihood of cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing).
